div(data-bind="if: page() == 'developers'")
    h1 Developers Welcome <small>built with open source</small>
    .row
        .col-md-6
            h5 Introduction
            p <strong>Malt</strong>.io loves developers and loves open source. The projects below form the basis of this site, from low-level conversion and calculations to backend <abbr title="Application Programming Interfaces">APIs</abbr> and live-updating web pages. Help to build the next killer homebrewing app!
        .col-md-6
            h5 What is Open Source?
            p Open source means that the entire computer code that is behind this website is open for anybody to download, share, add to or use in their own projects. <strong>Malt</strong>.io will always be open.
    .row
        .col-md-4
            h2 Brauhaus.js
            p <strong>Brauhaus</strong> is a javascript library for homebrew calculations that runs on both the server (<a href="http://nodejs.org/">Node.js</a>) and client (web browsers). It allows you to create and calculate recipes, do conversions, and much more.
        .col-md-4
            h2 Tapline
            p <strong>Tapline</strong> is an API server that wraps Brauhaus and <a href="http://www.mongodb.org/">MongoDB</a> to provide authentication, authorization, users, stored recipes, and recipe calculation functionality on-demand from any client that can speak <abbr title="Representational State Transfer">REST</abbr> and <abbr title="Javascript Object Notation">JSON</abbr>.
        .col-md-3
            h2 Malt.io
            p <strong>Malt</strong>.io is this website, which uses Tapline's API to fetch and store users and recipes. It also uses Brauhaus to live-update the page as you edit recipes on the site.
